1
00:00:15,799 --> 00:00:18,033
<i>Dying isn't easy.</i>

2
00:00:21,605 --> 00:00:25,040
<i>The body was
designed to stay alive.</i>

3
00:00:25,909 --> 00:00:28,577
<i>Thick skulls...</i>

4
00:00:28,678 --> 00:00:30,345
<i>strong hearts...</i>

5
00:00:31,498 --> 00:00:33,865
<i>keen senses.</i>

6
00:00:55,038 --> 00:00:58,974
Morning.

7
00:00:59,359 --> 00:01:00,959
Morning.

8
00:01:10,654 --> 00:01:13,188
<i>When the body starts to fail...</i>

9
00:01:14,141 --> 00:01:17,209
<i>medicine takes over.</i>

10
00:01:18,946 --> 00:01:22,814
Morning. Kim, Sean.
How're you feeling?

11
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:26,718
Ready. Today's the day.

12
00:01:27,338 --> 00:01:28,770
How are you doing?

13
00:01:29,439 --> 00:01:31,256
OK.

14
00:01:31,358 --> 00:01:34,209
<i>Surgeons are
arrogant enough to think</i>

15
00:01:34,311 --> 00:01:37,078
<i>there's no one we can't save.</i>

16
00:01:37,915 --> 00:01:39,614
- You need a consult?
- Kim Allan.

17
00:01:39,716 --> 00:01:41,728
She has stage-four
large cell lung cancer.

18
00:01:41,752 --> 00:01:44,631
I removed a second mass from
her right lung about two months ago,

19
00:01:44,655 --> 00:01:46,365
but tests show the
cancer had spread

20
00:01:46,389 --> 00:01:48,618
to her lymph nodes
and to her liver.

21
00:01:48,642 --> 00:01:51,927
She was readmitted last
week with pulmonary edema.

22
00:01:52,029 --> 00:01:53,306
I drained as much
fluid as I could,

23
00:01:53,330 --> 00:01:55,611
but she's having a
tough time breathing.

24
00:01:55,666 --> 00:01:58,200
That's too bad. You
gonna have to intubate her?

25
00:01:58,301 --> 00:02:01,236
- She doesn't want that.
- You have to treat her
palliatively.

26
00:02:01,338 --> 00:02:03,805
I don't see what else
we can do for her.

27
00:02:03,907 --> 00:02:07,475
- She wants us to help her die.
<i>- Like I said,</i>

28
00:02:07,578 --> 00:02:09,528
<i>dying isn't easy.</i>

29
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:15,600
Since the state requires
two physicians' signatures,

30
00:02:15,702 --> 00:02:18,062
I've asked Dr. Hunt
to look over your chart.

31
00:02:18,905 --> 00:02:20,855
OK.

32
00:02:20,957 --> 00:02:24,009
Her prognosis says that she
has less than six months to live.

33
00:02:24,111 --> 00:02:27,479
I have informed her of
her treatment options.

34
00:02:27,581 --> 00:02:30,215
She has met with a
psychologist who has determined

35
00:02:30,317 --> 00:02:32,183
that she is mentally fit.

36
00:02:32,285 --> 00:02:35,737
And this can serve as
her second oral request.

37
00:02:36,723 --> 00:02:39,507
OK.

38
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:42,444
You have to say it.

39
00:02:42,563 --> 00:02:45,096
Washington State says

40
00:02:45,199 --> 00:02:49,100
I have to hear you ask two
times at least 15 days apart.

41
00:02:49,185 --> 00:02:51,019
It's so weird.

42
00:02:51,121 --> 00:02:52,654
It's like I'm applying to die.

43
00:02:52,772 --> 00:02:54,067
If you're having
second thoughts...

44
00:02:54,091 --> 00:02:56,624
You saw how bad
it got last night.

45
00:02:56,726 --> 00:02:58,259
It's just gonna get worse.

46
00:03:01,148 --> 00:03:05,483
I would like to end my life

47
00:03:05,586 --> 00:03:08,086
through
physician-assisted suicide.

48
00:03:13,626 --> 00:03:14,959
Excuse me, um...

49
00:03:20,901 --> 00:03:23,001
I'm just gonna go see what's up.

50
00:03:23,103 --> 00:03:24,802
Dr. Altman?

51
00:03:25,805 --> 00:03:27,022
How long does it take?

52
00:03:27,124 --> 00:03:29,056
To die?

53
00:03:29,159 --> 00:03:30,458
Once I take the barbiturates.

54
00:03:30,578 --> 00:03:34,980
Can we not talk about
this? It's just, um...

55
00:03:35,849 --> 00:03:37,115
We're not there yet.

56
00:03:39,003 --> 00:03:40,869
We are there, Sean.

57
00:03:41,755 --> 00:03:43,488
We are.

58
00:03:46,477 --> 00:03:48,626
Kim, to answer your question...

59
00:03:49,929 --> 00:03:51,896
about 45 minutes.

60
00:03:52,932 --> 00:03:55,567
It takes about
45 minutes to die.

61
00:03:58,004 --> 00:04:00,872
Three dates. No
sex. Just talking.

62
00:04:00,974 --> 00:04:02,886
Do you have any idea
how much you can learn

63
00:04:02,910 --> 00:04:04,387
about someone if
you remain upright?

64
00:04:04,411 --> 00:04:07,178
I bet you didn't know Teddy
hates the word "moist."

65
00:04:07,281 --> 00:04:10,115
Hates it. Would really
prefer people say "damp."

66
00:04:10,217 --> 00:04:13,802
You hear me? I'm growing again.

67
00:04:13,904 --> 00:04:16,299
- I'm, like, grown.
- - She's making cartilage from scratch.

68
00:04:16,323 --> 00:04:19,691
She's preoccupied
these days. It's super hot.

69
00:04:19,793 --> 00:04:22,794
- I'm gonna be late.
- Bye.

70
00:04:26,199 --> 00:04:27,582
She doesn't want kids.

71
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:31,086
Arizona doesn't want kids. In
her womb, in her house. Ever.

72
00:04:31,188 --> 00:04:33,304
- She told me.
- What did you say?

73
00:04:33,390 --> 00:04:36,091
Nothing. We're doing so
great. I don't want to ruin it

74
00:04:36,193 --> 00:04:38,304
by being the crazy desperate
girl with the aching womb.

75
00:04:38,328 --> 00:04:40,078
Better than being the
crazy childless woman

76
00:04:40,180 --> 00:04:42,225
who sits at the playground
watching the children play.

77
00:04:42,249 --> 00:04:45,067
They have laws
for people like that.

78
00:04:45,169 --> 00:04:46,768
You gotta tell her.

79
00:04:49,572 --> 00:04:51,690
So in the third quarter
of the collection,

80
00:04:51,792 --> 00:04:54,025
rate of Medicaid was
what percent again?

81
00:04:55,012 --> 00:04:57,412
Hey. Would you
excuse me one second?

82
00:04:59,032 --> 00:05:00,966
OK. You have 30 seconds.

83
00:05:01,068 --> 00:05:03,651
OK. So this woman comes
into the ER with abdominal pain.

84
00:05:03,753 --> 00:05:06,015
She's had it on and
off for about six months,

85
00:05:06,039 --> 00:05:09,491
and a lot of doctors have told
her it's either an ulcer or gastritis.

86
00:05:09,593 --> 00:05:11,293
Get to the point.
You have 15 seconds.

87
00:05:11,395 --> 00:05:13,895
So it occurs to me that the
nausea is probably caused

88
00:05:13,997 --> 00:05:16,364
- by a positional shift...
- CSF. Brain tumor. Got it.

89
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:20,101
Not just any brain tumor. She's
got this huge, beautiful ependymoma.

90
00:05:20,203 --> 00:05:21,914
- So Shadow Shepherd...
- Dr. Nelson.

91
00:05:21,938 --> 00:05:26,024
OK, Shadow Shepherd is going
to do intraventricular resection

92
00:05:26,126 --> 00:05:27,542
and let me assist.

93
00:05:27,644 --> 00:05:29,956
And I may even get
to debulk the tumor.

94
00:05:29,980 --> 00:05:31,813
That's it?

95
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:34,582
OK, sorry for the interruption.

96
00:05:34,684 --> 00:05:36,217
So where were we?

97
00:05:36,319 --> 00:05:39,504
Percentage third quarter Medicaid.
What was the rate of return?

98
00:05:41,642 --> 00:05:43,219
- How close?
- Two minutes.

99
00:05:43,243 --> 00:05:46,004
- It's Nicole, right?
- Three guys waiting
on an ambulance?

100
00:05:46,062 --> 00:05:48,997
- Must be Nicole
behind the wheel.
- Have you seen her ass?

101
00:05:49,099 --> 00:05:50,465
Man, I'd love to hit that.

102
00:05:50,567 --> 00:05:54,486
- Morning, chief.
- Sorry about that, chief.

103
00:05:54,588 --> 00:05:56,938
It's quite all right.
And I am not the chief.

104
00:06:00,727 --> 00:06:02,476
- Hey, Nicole!
- Hey.

105
00:06:02,578 --> 00:06:05,664
Nick Kelsey, 32, injured
skiing off a helicopter.

106
00:06:05,766 --> 00:06:09,367
- Vital signs are stable.
- Wasn't the helicopter
that did it.

107
00:06:09,469 --> 00:06:11,330
- It was the avalanche.
- Idiotic either way.

108
00:06:11,354 --> 00:06:14,567
He's got two idiot friends coming in
behind him but he's got the worst of it.

109
00:06:14,591 --> 00:06:18,226
Open fracture to the left
tibia and left hip fracture.

110
00:06:22,249 --> 00:06:24,549
What are you looking at, chachi?

111
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:31,082
What happened? We were
in the middle of a consult.

112
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:33,474
You're her doctor. You
shouldn't push her to do that.

113
00:06:33,576 --> 00:06:36,661
I offered her options. I
told her about hospice.

114
00:06:36,746 --> 00:06:39,481
She doesn't want to die a slow
death hooked up to machines

115
00:06:39,582 --> 00:06:42,616
or be so heavily sedated
she might as well be dead.

116
00:06:42,719 --> 00:06:45,653
And I have to say, I don't
blame her. This is an act of mercy.

117
00:06:45,755 --> 00:06:48,390
Act of mercy? You're killing
her. Just so you're clear,

118
00:06:48,492 --> 00:06:51,959
by writing that prescription,
you're killing that woman.

119
00:06:54,147 --> 00:06:56,080
All right, then.

120
00:06:56,182 --> 00:07:01,269
I'll find someone else.

121
00:07:08,195 --> 00:07:10,045
Watch it, watch it! Heads up!

122
00:07:10,147 --> 00:07:13,343
You need to work on your
passing game, Hunt, you ball hog.

123
00:07:13,367 --> 00:07:15,233
You need to work on your game!

124
00:07:15,335 --> 00:07:17,736
- On your four!
- No!

125
00:07:17,838 --> 00:07:21,105
- Not a chance, major!
- Get it!

126
00:07:21,207 --> 00:07:24,810
- Watch out, watch out,
watch out!
- I got him! I got him!

127
00:07:30,650 --> 00:07:32,750
Break it up, break it
up, break it up, you two.

128
00:07:32,852 --> 00:07:35,403
- We're only down by three.
- Yeah, because you suck!

129
00:07:35,505 --> 00:07:36,971
Don't be insubordinate.

130
00:07:37,073 --> 00:07:38,406
Sir, you suck, sir.

131
00:07:38,508 --> 00:07:42,326
- I mean, Dan, you play
like my grandma.
- Whatever.

132
00:07:54,508 --> 00:07:57,342
Get your battle rattle.
Time to go to work.

133
00:08:07,287 --> 00:08:09,454
Owen, come on!

134
00:08:29,909 --> 00:08:32,522
I need to reduce this ankle
dislocation. Give him ten of morphine.

135
00:08:32,546 --> 00:08:34,990
We need to treat his frostbite.
You like the tips of your fingers?

136
00:08:35,014 --> 00:08:37,593
- Yes, please.
- You jumped out of
a helicopter on skis?

137
00:08:37,617 --> 00:08:40,001
Yeah. You can't get powder
like that anywhere else.

138
00:08:40,103 --> 00:08:42,069
I'm seeing fluid
around your kidney.

139
00:08:42,171 --> 00:08:44,272
We're gonna need to
do a CT of your abdomen.

140
00:08:44,374 --> 00:08:46,853
Do what you gotta do. Me and
the guys are running with the bulls

141
00:08:46,877 --> 00:08:50,244
in Pamplona next year.
Gotta be up on my feet.

142
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:57,785
Hey, Phil, tell those doctors
they need to fix you up

143
00:08:57,887 --> 00:09:00,655
so you can run with
the bulls next year!

144
00:09:00,757 --> 00:09:03,391
- You're an active guy.
- Once a year, anyhow.

145
00:09:03,493 --> 00:09:06,011
Better than nothing. Once
a year, we live like men.

146
00:09:06,113 --> 00:09:08,663
- You almost died like men.
- On my count.

147
00:09:08,765 --> 00:09:11,916
One, two, three!

148
00:09:13,186 --> 00:09:15,426
Big-ass car bomb
waxed half their unit.

149
00:09:15,488 --> 00:09:17,567
They tried to evac, but it
turned into an insurgent fire-fight.

150
00:09:17,591 --> 00:09:21,259
GSW to the abdomen. Let's
stabilize him till we get him to an OR.

151
00:09:21,361 --> 00:09:23,762
Get me some wet bandages
and an occlusive dressing.

152
00:09:23,864 --> 00:09:25,079
All out of those.

153
00:09:25,181 --> 00:09:29,017
OK, uh... some
wet towels and, uh...

154
00:09:29,119 --> 00:09:32,337
That. We'll close him with this.

155
00:09:34,591 --> 00:09:37,792
Gekko, give me that
roll of two-inch tape.

156
00:09:41,164 --> 00:09:43,815
I need a laryngoscope and
E-T tube. I need to intubate!

157
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:46,534
- Finish this!
- I'm on it!

158
00:09:46,636 --> 00:09:49,821
- Pupils fixed and dilated.
- He's way past go.

159
00:09:49,923 --> 00:09:51,772
- Who's next?
- Over here, sir!

160
00:09:51,874 --> 00:09:55,009
Colonel Mooney, sir, sandstorm's
coming. Command's ordered us to move.

161
00:09:55,111 --> 00:09:57,662
- You're kidding me. When?
- Now, sir.

162
00:09:57,764 --> 00:10:00,164
All right. People,
secure your patients.

163
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:01,660
I almost have my guy stabilized.

164
00:10:01,684 --> 00:10:03,029
You'll ride with him
on the medevac.

165
00:10:03,053 --> 00:10:05,169
Take my amputation
and the head trauma too.

166
00:10:05,272 --> 00:10:09,090
Hunt, we'll take your GSW
in the APC. Let's move!

167
00:10:10,359 --> 00:10:11,854
- Want me to go?
- No, I'm fine.

168
00:10:11,878 --> 00:10:14,612
- You hate helicopters.
- I know.

169
00:10:14,714 --> 00:10:17,498
I'm fine. I'll see
you back there.

170
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,633
- See you back there.
- Yep.

171
00:10:21,704 --> 00:10:24,038
Shall we scan him first?

172
00:10:27,193 --> 00:10:29,138
See what kind of
damage we're dealing with

173
00:10:29,162 --> 00:10:31,407
in case we need an OR. He's
got some abdominal bruising.

174
00:10:31,431 --> 00:10:34,548
Yeah. Yeah, OK. You take this.

175
00:10:35,618 --> 00:10:37,284
Uh, get him up to CT.

176
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:39,587
How come you didn't
get hurt in the avalanche?

177
00:10:39,689 --> 00:10:41,873
I never got off the
helicopter. I was about to jump

178
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:43,095
when the avalanche started.

179
00:10:43,126 --> 00:10:45,343
You missed it, Tommy.
Friggin' awesome!

180
00:10:45,445 --> 00:10:47,712
Yeah, Tommy, friggin' awesome!

181
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:50,899
Yeah, Tommy, friggin' awesome.

182
00:10:54,905 --> 00:10:57,739
Dr. Altman said you requested
to lower your pain meds?

183
00:10:57,841 --> 00:11:00,157
They make me fuzzy.

184
00:11:00,259 --> 00:11:02,610
I don't want to be fuzzy today.

185
00:11:02,712 --> 00:11:04,178
Did she tell you?

186
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:06,548
That you're going home? Yeah.

187
00:11:06,650 --> 00:11:08,366
- I changed my mind.
- What?

188
00:11:08,468 --> 00:11:10,551
No, no, not about...

189
00:11:10,653 --> 00:11:13,254
I just... I want to do it here.

190
00:11:13,356 --> 00:11:14,672
In the hospital.

191
00:11:14,774 --> 00:11:17,491
I don't want Sean to have to
deal with my body afterwards.

192
00:11:17,610 --> 00:11:18,804
Don't worry about that stuff.

193
00:11:18,828 --> 00:11:20,623
We can make this
place like home.

194
00:11:20,647 --> 00:11:23,614
You know? Get rid
of all these machines

195
00:11:23,716 --> 00:11:26,401
and get some of our stuff,

196
00:11:26,503 --> 00:11:29,787
my quilt, some pictures.

197
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:32,457
Some wine.

198
00:11:32,559 --> 00:11:36,377
- Can we have wine?
- I don't see why not.

199
00:11:36,479 --> 00:11:38,190
If you need wine, maybe
you don't really want...

200
00:11:38,214 --> 00:11:41,566
I don't need wine. I want wine.

201
00:11:41,668 --> 00:11:44,135
But I think you're
gonna need it.

202
00:11:44,237 --> 00:11:45,620
You seem scared.

203
00:11:46,773 --> 00:11:50,107
Are you... scared?

204
00:11:50,209 --> 00:11:51,459
Stop worrying about me.

205
00:11:51,561 --> 00:11:53,038
All these things are happening,

206
00:11:53,062 --> 00:11:55,007
and I'm making
all these choices,

207
00:11:55,031 --> 00:11:58,365
and I have no idea
how you're feeling.

208
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:00,651
- I'm not feeling anything.
- Sean!

209
00:12:00,753 --> 00:12:03,165
I'm talking about
where I'm gonna die.

210
00:12:03,189 --> 00:12:05,890
You have to be
feeling something!

211
00:12:10,363 --> 00:12:12,096
I'll go home and get the stuff.

212
00:12:12,198 --> 00:12:13,515
Sean...

213
00:12:15,752 --> 00:12:17,484
Red or white?

214
00:12:18,905 --> 00:12:21,205
Red.

215
00:12:21,307 --> 00:12:23,841
In a wine glass,
not a plastic cup.

216
00:12:23,926 --> 00:12:26,010
OK.

217
00:12:29,048 --> 00:12:31,716
It never changes.

218
00:12:31,818 --> 00:12:35,770
You have the same fights. I
mean, even when you're dying,

219
00:12:35,872 --> 00:12:37,488
you have the same fights.

220
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:39,485
You want to know
how they're feeling,

221
00:12:39,509 --> 00:12:41,476
and they don't want to tell you.

222
00:12:42,212 --> 00:12:44,546
- Sorry.
- Don't be.

223
00:12:48,184 --> 00:12:49,783
I think they don't know.

224
00:12:49,886 --> 00:12:51,397
When you ask them
how they're feeling,

225
00:12:51,421 --> 00:12:53,315
and they don't want to tell you,

226
00:12:53,339 --> 00:12:55,723
and you think
they're being difficult?

227
00:12:55,825 --> 00:12:58,065
I think they really don't know.

228
00:13:00,730 --> 00:13:04,631
OK, relax. Deep
breaths. Deep breaths.

229
00:13:06,236 --> 00:13:07,468
Good.

230
00:13:13,660 --> 00:13:16,427
Where do you stand on
physician-assisted suicide?

231
00:13:16,529 --> 00:13:17,695
I'm not opposed to it.

232
00:13:17,797 --> 00:13:19,791
As long as we're talking
about controversial stuff,

233
00:13:19,815 --> 00:13:22,550
let's get something straight:
Arena Football is not real football.

234
00:13:22,652 --> 00:13:24,452
Mark. Mark, wait.

235
00:13:24,554 --> 00:13:28,322
This is not me getting
to know you. This is...

236
00:13:29,559 --> 00:13:31,637
I have a patient who's terminal.

237
00:13:31,661 --> 00:13:35,530
She wants to die, and she
wants my help. And I want yours.

238
00:13:41,104 --> 00:13:43,337
See that? The tumor's
pressing down on the floor

239
00:13:43,439 --> 00:13:45,907
of the fourth ventricle,
which is causing the nausea.

240
00:13:46,008 --> 00:13:49,310
So you debulk the tumor, and
then you move on to the stalk?

241
00:13:49,412 --> 00:13:51,279
No. You debulk the tumor.

242
00:13:51,381 --> 00:13:54,615
Dr. Shepherd has requested these
scans. His schedule has freed up.

243
00:13:54,717 --> 00:13:56,245
He's decided to do
the resection himself.

