00:29:25,013 --> 00:29:26,779
We can make you comfortable.

485
00:29:27,850 --> 00:29:29,599
- I just have one question.
- Owen, no.

486
00:29:29,701 --> 00:29:32,185
What if they find a cure? I
know that it's a long shot,

487
00:29:32,287 --> 00:29:34,987
but isn't saving your life
worth gambling on a long shot?

488
00:29:35,107 --> 00:29:38,892
- Dr. Hunt, I will
call security if...
- Let her answer.

489
00:29:40,128 --> 00:29:42,196
I'd like to hear the answer.

490
00:29:45,885 --> 00:29:48,451
Maybe...

491
00:29:48,553 --> 00:29:51,255
you have to be
dying to understand,

492
00:29:51,356 --> 00:29:54,324
but there's this
thing that happens...

493
00:29:55,694 --> 00:29:59,029
where death stops being scary.

494
00:30:00,900 --> 00:30:03,967
What starts being scary is hope.

495
00:30:05,737 --> 00:30:07,604
'Cause it's not true.

496
00:30:11,643 --> 00:30:14,944
Even if they found a
cure for cancer tomorrow...

497
00:30:16,215 --> 00:30:18,515
it's too late for me.

498
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:24,570
And hanging onto hope, it
may make you feel better...

499
00:30:28,410 --> 00:30:31,245
but it just makes me feel alone.

500
00:30:38,504 --> 00:30:40,703
I don't want to die alone.

501
00:30:43,024 --> 00:30:44,791
OK?

502
00:30:51,416 --> 00:30:55,485
I am not afraid of this.

503
00:30:55,587 --> 00:30:57,003
Why are you?

504
00:30:59,774 --> 00:31:03,176
Why are you so
afraid to let me die?

505
00:31:25,767 --> 00:31:27,083
Dr. Hunt?

506
00:31:28,637 --> 00:31:31,938
The pharmacy wouldn't
take my insurance card.

507
00:31:33,208 --> 00:31:34,488
There was some problem,

508
00:31:34,543 --> 00:31:37,527
so I had to go to
a cash machine.

509
00:31:37,629 --> 00:31:41,364
And I'm running around
trying to get enough cash

510
00:31:41,466 --> 00:31:44,134
to buy the pills that
are gonna kill my wife.

511
00:31:47,122 --> 00:31:49,456
Anyway...

512
00:31:50,892 --> 00:31:52,158
here they are.

513
00:32:09,594 --> 00:32:11,394
There'll be a moment...

514
00:32:13,364 --> 00:32:15,982
when she dies, her
face will relax, and...

515
00:32:17,919 --> 00:32:20,453
all that pain that she
was in will be gone.

516
00:32:23,592 --> 00:32:25,725
And you will feel relief.

517
00:32:27,529 --> 00:32:29,862
Relief for her, relief for you.

518
00:32:29,964 --> 00:32:33,866
You will know with
absolute certainty

519
00:32:33,968 --> 00:32:36,236
that you did the right thing.

520
00:32:42,027 --> 00:32:43,927
Just for a moment.

521
00:32:45,530 --> 00:32:48,665
You gotta let me go, Owen.

522
00:32:48,767 --> 00:32:51,601
OK? You gotta let me
go, please. This hurts.

523
00:32:51,703 --> 00:32:53,053
It hurts.

524
00:32:53,855 --> 00:32:56,590
It's OK. It's OK.

525
00:32:56,692 --> 00:33:01,111
It's OK. Look at me.
OK. You gotta do it.

526
00:33:01,213 --> 00:33:03,195
You gotta do it. I
can't make you do it.

527
00:33:03,965 --> 00:33:06,566
OK. Please, it hurts.

528
00:33:06,668 --> 00:33:10,220
It hurts. It hurts, it's OK.

529
00:33:10,322 --> 00:33:15,709
It's OK. It's OK.
OK. You gotta do it.

530
00:33:40,418 --> 00:33:42,785
You have to hold
on to that moment,

531
00:33:42,888 --> 00:33:47,891
because all the rest of it
is just your own garbage.

532
00:33:57,319 --> 00:33:59,736
You'll be in physical
therapy for six months,

533
00:33:59,838 --> 00:34:03,472
but, with luck, you'll be
ready for your trip next year.

534
00:34:03,575 --> 00:34:07,410
- Pamplona, baby!
- Pamplona!

535
00:34:07,512 --> 00:34:08,861
Pamplona!

536
00:34:10,031 --> 00:34:11,798
Oh, come on.

537
00:34:11,900 --> 00:34:13,699
He hates this stuff.

538
00:34:13,801 --> 00:34:17,220
The adrenaline, the adventure.
He does this just for you guys

539
00:34:17,322 --> 00:34:19,673
because you guys
love it, and he loves you.

540
00:34:20,642 --> 00:34:25,278
And... that's my
rant for the day.

541
00:34:25,380 --> 00:34:28,231
I'm sorry. I like to see people
keep their legs. Ignore me.

542
00:34:28,333 --> 00:34:30,249
I'm starting my own business.

543
00:34:32,153 --> 00:34:34,321
Keeps my blood pumping.

544
00:34:34,423 --> 00:34:37,991
I'm with Tommy.

545
00:34:40,928 --> 00:34:42,178
Sorry, Nick.

546
00:34:44,783 --> 00:34:48,901
I can't believe you guys.
I almost died jumping out

547
00:34:49,003 --> 00:34:54,424
of a helicopter when I wanted
to go wine-tasting in Napa.

548
00:35:00,682 --> 00:35:01,948
Napa!

549
00:35:05,304 --> 00:35:07,838
Napa!

550
00:35:20,919 --> 00:35:24,955
Place looks different.
Something's different.

551
00:35:25,056 --> 00:35:27,757
- Something I can help you with?
- You were jealous of her today.

552
00:35:27,860 --> 00:35:29,793
- I'm sorry?
- Meredith.

553
00:35:29,895 --> 00:35:32,245
That's why you
stole her surgery.

554
00:35:32,347 --> 00:35:36,383
You miss the pace of back-to-back
surgeries, the adrenaline.

555
00:35:38,854 --> 00:35:40,387
Yeah, I do.

556
00:35:44,993 --> 00:35:47,433
Schedule yourself
one surgery a day.

557
00:35:47,495 --> 00:35:49,896
In the morning, early, an
hour before anyone else.

558
00:35:49,998 --> 00:35:52,293
So at the very least,
you start your day good,

559
00:35:52,317 --> 00:35:54,262
you start your day cutting.

560
00:35:54,286 --> 00:35:56,413
You don't have to
sign all the paperwork.

561
00:35:56,437 --> 00:35:58,582
Patricia is an excellent forger.

562
00:35:58,606 --> 00:36:01,235
If you eat alone in the
cafeteria, you are a sitting duck.

563
00:36:01,259 --> 00:36:02,887
You need to eat
with someone else.

564
00:36:02,911 --> 00:36:05,862
That way, people are more
likely to leave you alone.

565
00:36:09,768 --> 00:36:12,002
You can eat with me.

566
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:16,789
Thank you.

567
00:36:16,891 --> 00:36:19,492
<i>Living is better than dying.</i>

568
00:36:22,214 --> 00:36:23,980
<i>Until it's not.</i>

569
00:36:51,543 --> 00:36:53,309
I'm scared.

570
00:36:54,429 --> 00:36:56,229
Come here.

571
00:37:08,527 --> 00:37:13,245
<i>But even if letting a person
die is the right thing to do...</i>

572
00:37:16,267 --> 00:37:19,201
<i>it's not what
surgeons are built for.</i>

573
00:37:21,272 --> 00:37:23,940
<i>We are arrogant and competitive.</i>

574
00:37:30,048 --> 00:37:33,082
I'm sorry.

575
00:37:34,852 --> 00:37:36,653
I know you're mad at me.

576
00:37:42,777 --> 00:37:44,577
I'm not mad.

577
00:37:44,679 --> 00:37:47,630
- I'm in Whoville.
- Whoville?

578
00:37:47,716 --> 00:37:49,999
Whoville.

579
00:37:54,622 --> 00:37:56,656
<i>We don't like to lose.</i>

580
00:38:01,729 --> 00:38:03,430
Um...

581
00:38:04,632 --> 00:38:06,210
This is really
hard for me to say

582
00:38:06,234 --> 00:38:10,019
'cause I really care
about you and...

583
00:38:10,122 --> 00:38:12,655
Oh, my God, you're
breaking up with me.

584
00:38:12,757 --> 00:38:15,391
Mark? Is it Mark? Are you
sleeping with Mark again?

585
00:38:15,476 --> 00:38:19,228
Are you one of those fake lesbians
having a vacation in lesbian land?

586
00:38:19,331 --> 00:38:21,297
No. Stop.

587
00:38:23,167 --> 00:38:25,502
God, it's not bad.

588
00:38:26,905 --> 00:38:29,425
This thing I have
to tell you isn't bad.

589
00:38:30,007 --> 00:38:32,642
Um... I just...

590
00:38:34,479 --> 00:38:39,415
I want to have a baby.
At some point in my life.

591
00:38:40,302 --> 00:38:42,118
That's all.

592
00:38:43,287 --> 00:38:47,206
I really... I have
to have a baby.

593
00:38:48,610 --> 00:38:52,545
<i>And death feels like a loss...</i>

594
00:38:55,283 --> 00:38:56,882
<i>even when we know it's not.</i>

595
00:38:59,220 --> 00:39:01,805
<i>We know it's time.</i>

596
00:39:01,907 --> 00:39:04,273
- <i>We know it's right.</i>
- Hey, there.

597
00:39:04,876 --> 00:39:07,776
- Hey.
- Come in.

598
00:39:12,667 --> 00:39:15,117
I helped my patient die today.

599
00:39:16,454 --> 00:39:19,288
You wanna talk about it?

600
00:39:19,390 --> 00:39:24,276
No.

601
00:39:27,615 --> 00:39:30,683
<i>We know we did
everything we could.</i>

602
00:39:40,095 --> 00:39:43,062
It's OK. You gotta do it.

603
00:39:44,365 --> 00:39:46,732
You gotta do it. I
can't make you do it.

604
00:39:47,936 --> 00:39:49,635
You gotta do it.

605
00:39:50,772 --> 00:39:52,505
OK.

606
00:41:07,665 --> 00:41:09,031
What are you...?

607
00:41:11,586 --> 00:41:13,286
I couldn't sleep.

608
00:41:15,807 --> 00:41:16,873
Are you OK?

609
00:41:16,975 --> 00:41:20,309
<i>But it's hard to
shake the feeling</i>

610
00:41:20,411 --> 00:41:22,762
<i>that you could have done more.</i>

611
00:41:22,864 --> 00:41:26,716
Yeah. I'm fine. Go back to bed.

612
00:41:29,070 --> 00:41:30,703
Owen...

613
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:34,891
- What are you thinking?
- Nothing.

614
00:41:36,161 --> 00:41:37,927
Nothing.

615
00:41:39,798 --> 00:41:41,430
Go back to bed.
